Directive are used for specifying something for the whole page
Types of Directive:
@page --> for adding package
@include --> used to include the existing JSP Page in Page
@taglib --> for proviiding tags that are beyond the html


1. @page:

Syntax:
<%@ page attribute="value" attribute="value" %>

Attributes:

language="scripting language"  --> by default: JAVA 
extends="className"            
import="importList"             --> for packages we can use
session="true|false"
autoFlush="true|false"
contentType="ctiinfo"
errorPage="errorUrl"
isErrorPage="true|false"
info="information"
isELIgnored="true|false"
isThreadSafe="true|False"


Ex:

<%@ page language="java" import="java.sql.Statement, java.util.Scanner"%>


2. @include --> just like we use in php for header and footer

    <%a include file="header.jsp" %>
    
    
3. @taglib

    to include the library
    suppose we want to use our own library H1 Tag or modify h1 tag of html
    <%@ taglib uri="uri" prefix="fx" %>
    <fx:h1>
    
    
